1
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:39,478
- Bull's-eye!
- You bet, Dad!

2
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,948
You go straight home.

3
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,030
Okay!

4
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,518
Bombs away!

5
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,990
JEDEDIAH:
Sayonara, sucker!

6
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:25,597
WATERSELLER:
No preservatives, just pure water!

7
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:28,110
WATERSELLER:
Cool, clear water.

8
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,755
Step up, schmuck, get some dealing done.

9
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,911
H20, that's my go.

10
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:37,068
Don't you understand? This is water.
You can't live without it.

11
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:44,993
What's a little fallout, huh?
Have a nice day!

12
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,553
COLLECTOR:
You get a sack of grain...

13
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:06,190
...or a woman for two hours.

14
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,716
COLLECTOR: What are you trading?
MAX: I'm looking for someone.

15
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,279
COLLECTOR:
Are you trading or not?

16
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,669
He had a team of camels.

17
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:23,631
COLLECTOR: People come here to trade,
make a little profit, do some business.

18
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,108
If you've nothing to trade,
you've no business here.

19
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,349
An hour inside.

20
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,594
- Next!
- I got skills I can trade.

21
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,237
Sorry. The brothel's full.

22
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,314
One hour.

23
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,472
- And if you find him?
- I'll ask him to return what's mine.

24
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:59,320
And he'll be desperate
to clear his conscience.

25
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,549
He will be.

26
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,672
You're that good?

27
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:07,799
Perhaps you have something to trade
after all.

28
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,269
Keep talking.

29
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,950
24 hours of your life.

30
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,994
In return,
you'll get back what was stolen.

31
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,073
Sounds like a bargain.

32
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:21,353
It's not. Let's talk.
Come inside.

33
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:37,429
COLLECTOR: Leave your weapons here.
It's the law.

34
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:11,152
DR. DEALGOOD: Remember, this is the
vehicle that sent Detroit broke.

35
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,512
MAX:
Where did you get these animals?

36
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:17,558
DR. DEALGOOD: The glorious dromedary.
The ship of the desert.

37
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:22,556
They've got independent suspension,
power steering and no emission control.

38
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,068
Ride them away now.

39
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:10,480
(SAXOPHONE PLA YS)

40
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,833
(SAXOPHONE PLA YS)

41
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,308
COLLECTOR:
A warrior, Aunty.

42
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:46,038
COLLECTOR: Lost everything.
Looking for a deal.

43
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,270
But he's just a raggedy man.

44
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:54,554
He's quick.

45
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,070
Ironbar...

46
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,959
...can he do it?

47
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,036
Maybe.

48
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,592
AUNTY:
What did you do before this?

49
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,990
I was a cop, a driver.

50
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,711
But how the world turns.

51
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,520
One day cock of the walk,
next, a feather duster.

52
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:21,479
Play something tragic, Ton Ton.

53
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,198
Do you know who I was?

54
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,035
Nobody.

55
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:33,877
Except on the day after,
I was still alive.

56
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:37,274
This nobody had a chance to be somebody.

57
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,834
So much for history. Anyway...
Water? Fruit?

58
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,558
Congratulations. You're the first
to survive the audition.

59
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,035
Drink.

60
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,509
It's okay.

61
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,995
AUNTY:
Come with me.

62
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:03,359
AUNTY:
Look around. All this I built.

63
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,308
Up to my armpits in blood and shit.

64
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,590
Where there was desert,
now there's a town.

65
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:13,431
Where there was robbery,
there's trade.

66
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,919
Where there was despair,
now there's hope.

67
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,839
It's civilization.

68
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:21,715
I'll do anything to protect it.

69
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:27,676
Today it's necessary to kill a man.
What do you say?

70
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:30,875
What do you pay?

71
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:36,112
I'll re-equip you...
Vehicles, animals. Fuel, if you want.

72
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,719
It's a generous offer.

73
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:41,077
Why me? You've got warriors,
weapons. Give the order.

74
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,034
We are dealing with subtleties here.

75
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,670
This is no enemy.
It's almost family.

76
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,072
I see, real civilized.

77
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:53,269
The reasons don't concern you,
just the conditions. Deal?

78
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:58,518
First, no one knows
you're working for Aunty.

79
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,910
You hit him, you go.

80
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:03,510
Second, it's a fair fight.

81
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,030
And third, it's to the death.

82
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,399
Who's the bunny?

83
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:48,395
It's called Underworld.
It's where Bartertown gets its energy.

84
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,239
Oil, natural gas?

85
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:51,954
AUNTY:
Pigs.

86
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,112
MAX:
Pigs like those?

87
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,550
- Bullshit.
- Pigshit.

88
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:01,749
Pigshit. The lights,
the motors, the vehicles...

89
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:05,430
...all run by a high-powered gas
called methane.

90
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:08,589
Methane comes from pigshit.

91
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,634
Have a look.
Tell me what you see.

92
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:17,757
MAX: I see a big guy
giving a little guy a piggyback.

93
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,715
AUNTY:
MasterBlaster. They're a unit.

94
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,916
They even share the same name.

95
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:26,755
COLLECTOR: The little one is called
Master. He's the brains.

96
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,957
He runs Underworld.

97
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:33,075
COLLECTOR: The other one is Blaster.
He's the muscle.

98
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,949
Together they can be very powerful.

99
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,750
They are also arrogant.

100
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:44,916
We want to keep the brain,
dump the body.

101
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,912
He's big. Is he good?

102
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:50,680
He can beat most men with his breath.

103
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,480
I want a closer look at him.
How do I get in there?

104
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:56,553
- lt's a factory. Ask for work.
- I know nothing about methane.

105
00:15:57,880 --> 00:15:59,711
You can shovel shit, can't you?

106
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,999
Hey, you!

107
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:48,914
MAX:
Let's talk!

108
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:56,593
Here, free man, come help a convict.
You don't want to end up like me.

109
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,513
MAX:
How long are you in for?

110
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,512
The big one. Life.

111
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:02,910
For killing a pig?

112
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,277
PIGKILLER:
I had to feed the kids.

113
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:09,599
Doesn't worry me. Down here
life's two, three years.

114
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:25,757
MASTER:
Where is that bum mechanic Blackfinger?

115
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:37,878
BLACKFINGER:
We got a real problem.

116
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,668
Twelve pounds of dynamite set to blow.

117
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,155
You expert! Disarm!

118
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,709
Right.

119
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:01,718
It's a class job. One mistake,
it'll blow the crap out of this place.

120
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,309
- Literally.
- Think what to do!

121
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:10,555
Now...the dynamite is connected
to the timing device...

122
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:13,752
...which is connected to the switch,
which I can't find...

123
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,838
...which is connected to the...

124
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,235
...battery.

125
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:21,632
- I'll disconnect the battery!
- I wouldn't do that.

126
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,518
MASTER:
Who you?

127
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,352
- Me Max.
- You smart.

128
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,154
That's my vehicle.

129
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:30,350
Disarm!

130
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:31,830
How much?

131
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,991
No trade. Do!

132
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:37,675
Fetch!

133
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:45,911
Me order. Me Master!

134
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:48,516
Me run Bartertown!

135
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,998
That's why you live in shit.

136
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,271
Not shit! Energy!

137
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,474
Call it what you like,
it still smells like shit.

138
00:18:56,760 --> 00:19:00,753
Not shit! Energy!
No energy, no town!

139
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,276
Me King Arab!

140
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:05,078
Sure. Me, fairy princess.

141
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,159
Embargo, on!

142
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:29,473
MASTER:
Embargo on! Main valve off!

143
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:47,077
Four, three, two...

144
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,518
(AUNTY OVER SPEAKER)
For God's sake, what now?

145
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:52,470
Who run Bartertown?

146
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,468
Damn it!
I told you, no more embargos.

147
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:58,916
More, Blaster.

148
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,719
Who run Bartertown?

149
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:14,113
(MASTER OVER SPEAKER)
Who run Bartertown?

150
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,392
You know who.

151
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,955
Say.

152
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,513
MasterBlaster.

153
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,435
Say loud.

154
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,228
MasterBlaster.

155
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,634
(MASTER OVER SPEAKER)
MasterBlaster what?

156
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,719
(AUNTY OVER SPEAKER)
MasterBlaster runs Bartertown.

157
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,393
(MASTER OVER SPEAKER)
Louder!

158
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,353
MasterBlaster runs Bartertown.

159
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,870
Lift embargo.

160
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,036
You want foot in face?

161
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:14,919
Disarm.

162
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,632
Good boy.

163
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,518
Over here, Blaster.

164
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:23,549
- What are you laying for?
- Nothing.

165
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:24,995
- Who are you?
- Nobody.

166
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:28,994
No, mister, I can feel it.
The dice are rolling!

167
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:38,476
I want my camels, my vehicle,
food, water, methane.

168
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,431
- Deal.
- You said a fair fight.

169
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:45,956
- What does that mean?
- As provided by law.

170
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,595
Thunderdome.

171
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:56,032
AUNTY: Two men, hand-to-hand.
No jury, no appeal, no parole.

172
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:58,277
Two men enter, one man leaves.

173
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,309
Weapons?

174
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,672
Anything's possible.
Chance decides.

175
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:07,874
Thunderdome.
How do I get in there?

176
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:10,475
That's easy. Pick a fight.

177
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:48,390
MASTER:
Everybody have a good time!

178
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:54,316
That's my vehicle
and I want it back!

179
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:56,990
Hearing wonky.
Sounds like an order.

180
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,075
That's right.

181
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:03,553
Yumping Yesus! Him sad.
Brain broken.

182
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,918
Me explain.

183
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,399
This my vehicle. You...

184
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,512
...pedestrian!

185
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:17,875
MASTER:
Three seconds...

186
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,992
...break neck. One...

187
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:31,308
IRONBAR:
MasterBlaster!

188
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:33,950
Listen to the law!

189
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:37,517
COLLECTOR:
Aunty, two men in dispute.

190
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,915
MASTER:
These our witness, Aunty.

191
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:46,636
Us suffer bad.
Us want justice.

192
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:49,753
We want Thunderdome!

193
00:24:50,320 --> 00:24:54,108
AUNTY: You know the law.
Two men enter, one man leaves.

194
00:24:56,680 --> 00:25:01,470
This Blaster.
Twenty men enter, only him leave.

195
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:04,793
Then it's your choice.
Thunderdome.

196
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,718
CROWD:
Aunty! Aunty!

197
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:46,914
Welcome to another edition
of Thunderdome!

198
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:48,958
(CROWD CHEERS)

199
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:12,675
Listen on! Listen on!

200
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,072
This is the truth of it.

201
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:19,433
Fighting leads to killing,
and killing gets to warring.

202
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:22,712
And that was damn near
the death of us all.

203
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:27,872
Look at us now, busted up
and everyone talking about hard rain.

204
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:32,837
But we've learned by the dust
of them all. Bartertown's learned.

205
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:36,511
Now when men get to fighting,
it happens here.

206
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,796
And it finishes here.

207
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:42,914
Two men enter, one man leaves.

208
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,197
(CROWD CHANTS)
Two men enter, one man leaves.

209
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:09,710
DR. DEALGOOD: And right now,
I've got two men.

210
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,473
Two men with a gut full of fear.

211
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:18,598
Ladies and gentlemen, boys and girls...

212
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,195
...dying time's here!

213
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:28,037
He's the ball cracker.
Death on foot.

214
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:32,269
You know him. You love him!
He's Blaster!

215
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,471
(CROWD CHEERS)

216
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:46,470
The challenger,
direct from out of the Wasteland.

217
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:49,672
He's bad. He's beautiful.
He's crazy!

218
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,239
It's the man with no name!

219
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:55,556
(CROWD CHEERS)

220
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:49,959
Thunderdome's simple. Get to the
weapons, use them anyway you can.

221
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:53,676
I know you won't break the rules.
There aren't any.

222
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,029
Remember where you are.

223
00:29:01,320 --> 00:29:02,639
This is Thunderdome.

224
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:07,551
Death is listening, and will take
the first man that screams.

225
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:10,794
Prepare!

226
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,355
(CROWD CHANTS)
Two men enter, one man leaves!

227
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:36,113
(MAN SCREAMS)

228
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,474
(CROWD CHANTS)
Kill him!

229
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,597
- You know the law!
- This is Thunderdome!

230
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:25,630
Kill him!

231
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:28,838
No, no! Look at his face!

232
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:31,313
He's got the mind of a child.

233
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,158
It's not his fault.

234
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,277
Blaster, I'm sorry.

235
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,638
This wasn't part of the deal.

236
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:46,110
MASTER:
Deal?

237
00:34:48,680 --> 00:34:50,318
What do you mean, "deal"?

238
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:55,230
You must have tasted it.
It was in your hands.

239
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:56,995
AUNTY:
You had it all!

240
00:34:58,200 --> 00:34:59,679
What do you mean, "deal"?

241
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:05,393
MASTER:
No more methane!

242
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:08,520
This place...finished!

243
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:09,988
IRONBAR:
No, little man.

244
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:11,873
We've only just begun.

245
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:19,353
MASTER:
Oh, no.

246
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:21,353
MASTER:
No, no.

247
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:38,755
MAX:
Open it.

248
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,476
Two men enter. One man leaves!

249
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:48,598
(CROWD CHANTS)
Two men enter. One man leaves!

250
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:21,517
What's this?!

251
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:28,038
Do you think I don't know the law?
Wasn't it me who wrote it?

252
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,920
And this man has broken the law.

253
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:33,157
Right or wrong, we had a deal.

254
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:36,951
And the law says,
