GEKK O:
Not with wordstuff, with sonic.

284
00:47:12,280 --> 00:47:15,113
MR, SKYFISH: That ain't never gonna
work, sonic-bonic bullshit!

285
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:19,911
GEKK O:
This is Delta-Fox-X-Ray.

286
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:21,554
Can you hear me?

287
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:23,913
Delta-Fox-X-Ray.

288
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:27,074
Come in.

289
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:30,518
Is anybody out there?

290
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:35,275
Can you read me, Walker?

291
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:38,073
Delta-Fox-X-Ray.

292
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,269
Come in.

293
00:47:56,080 --> 00:47:57,559
What's up, Doc?

294
00:47:59,480 --> 00:48:01,516
Hey, take me with you!

295
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:05,558
GEKK O:
Can you hear me, Walker?

296
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:46,117
(MAX AND KIDS SCREAM)

297
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:03,592
GIRL:
Fly, Walker!

298
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:06,275
(KIDS CHANT)
Fly, Walker, fly!

299
00:49:42,360 --> 00:49:43,793
Who are you?

300
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:46,959
Quiet!

301
00:49:49,200 --> 00:49:50,679
Shut up!

302
00:49:54,800 --> 00:49:56,711
MAX:
Enough!

303
00:50:33,840 --> 00:50:35,319
Who are you?

304
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:38,679
The waiting ones.

305
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:40,075
Waiting for what?

306
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:41,628
Waiting for you.

307
00:50:43,080 --> 00:50:43,990
And who am I?

308
00:50:48,440 --> 00:50:50,476
I think he be testing us.

309
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:54,953
This a testing, Walker?
You reckon we been slack?

310
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,717
I don't know.
Maybe you've been slack.

311
00:50:58,520 --> 00:51:02,354
We ain't. We kept it straight.
It's all there.

312
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:06,792
Everything marked, everything
'membered. You wait, you'll see.

313
00:51:14,680 --> 00:51:17,558
This you knows.
I be First Tracker.

314
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:20,189
Times past count I done the Tell.

315
00:51:20,880 --> 00:51:25,192
But it weren't me that tumbled Walker.
It was Savannah.

316
00:51:25,840 --> 00:51:28,593
So it's only right
that she take the Tell.

317
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:35,318
This ain't one body's story.
It's the story of us all.

318
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:39,110
We got it mouth-to-mouth.
You got to listen it and 'member.

319
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:43,234
'Cause what you hears today
you got to tell the birthed tomorrow.

320
00:51:44,280 --> 00:51:46,396
I'm looking behind us now...

321
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:48,711
...across the count of time...

322
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:52,715
...down the long haul,
into history back.

323
00:51:53,040 --> 00:51:55,918
I sees the end what were the start.

324
00:51:56,280 --> 00:51:59,113
It's Pox-Eclipse, full of pain!

325
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:12,077
And out of it were birthed
crackling dust and fearsome time.

326
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:13,753
It were full-on winter...

327
00:52:14,160 --> 00:52:16,037
...and Mr. Dead chasing them all.

328
00:52:16,440 --> 00:52:20,274
But one he couldn't catch.
That were Captain Walker.

329
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:25,037
He gathers up a gang, takes to the air
and flies to the sky!

330
00:52:26,640 --> 00:52:31,111
So they left their homes,
said bidey-bye to the high-scrapers...

331
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:34,956
...and what were left of the knowing,
they left behind.

332
00:52:35,960 --> 00:52:38,155
Some say the wind just stoppered.

333
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:41,717
Others reckon it were a gang
called Turbulence.

334
00:52:48,160 --> 00:52:49,513
And after the wreck...

335
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:52,150
...some had been jumped by Mr. Dead...

336
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:56,354
...but some had got the luck,
and it leads them here.

337
00:52:56,840 --> 00:53:01,595
One look and they's got the hots for it.
They word it "Planet Earth."

338
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:05,914
And they says, "We don't need
the knowing. We can live here."

339
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:09,637
"We don't need the knowing.
We can live here."

340
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:13,917
SA VANNAH:
Time counts and keeps counting.

341
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:16,158
They gets missing what they had.

342
00:53:16,480 --> 00:53:19,950
They get so lonely for the
high-scrapers and the video.

343
00:53:20,240 --> 00:53:21,559
Videos!

344
00:53:25,640 --> 00:53:30,077
SA VANNAH: And they do pictures so they
'member all the knowing they lost.

345
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,435
SLAKE:
'Member this?

346
00:53:41,720 --> 00:53:43,790
KIDS:
Tomorrow-morrow Land!

347
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:45,639
SLAKE:
'Member this?

348
00:53:45,920 --> 00:53:47,672
KIDS:
The River of Light!

349
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:49,115
SLAKE:
'Member this?

350
00:53:49,400 --> 00:53:51,038
KIDS:
Skyraft!

351
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:52,275
SLAKE:
'Member this?

352
00:53:52,640 --> 00:53:54,596
KIDS:
Captain Walker!

353
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:56,239
SLAKE:
'Member this?

354
00:53:56,480 --> 00:53:57,469
KIDS:
Mrs. Walker!

355
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:00,513
(KIDS CHANT)

356
00:54:01,120 --> 00:54:05,591
Then Captain Walker picked them
of an age and good for a long haul.

357
00:54:06,080 --> 00:54:10,517
They counted twenty, and that were them.
The great leaving.

358
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:13,797
KIDS: "Rescue party departed
at first light...

359
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:17,117
...led by Flight Captain G.L. Walker."

360
00:54:17,360 --> 00:54:20,511
"May God have mercy on our souls."

361
00:54:21,600 --> 00:54:24,160
They said bidey-bye to them
what they'd birthed.

362
00:54:24,520 --> 00:54:26,715
And from the nothing
they looked back...

363
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:30,669
...and Captain Walker hollered,
"Wait, one of us will come."

364
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:33,919
"Wait, one of us will come."

365
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:38,275
And somebody did come.

366
00:54:38,760 --> 00:54:40,557
(KIDS CHANT)
Walker.

367
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:06,390
We's heartful to you,
Captain Walker.

368
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:09,234
We's ready now. Take us home.

369
00:55:18,280 --> 00:55:22,273
We kept it straight!
Everything marked, everything 'membered!

370
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:25,120
MAX: You kept it real good.
You ain't been slack.

371
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:27,357
GEKK O: Why are we waiting?
MAX: That ain't me.

372
00:55:27,600 --> 00:55:29,989
- You got the wrong guy.
MR. SKYFISH: Quit joshing!

373
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:32,954
- Catch the wind.
- We got to see Tomorrow-morrow Land!

374
00:55:33,320 --> 00:55:35,390
Home! Tomorrow-morrow Land!

375
00:55:41,480 --> 00:55:44,040
There were places like these.
Cities.

376
00:55:44,280 --> 00:55:46,350
They were called cities.

377
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:49,919
They had lots of knowing.
They had skyscrapers...

378
00:55:50,720 --> 00:55:52,870
...videos and they had the sonic.

379
00:55:55,840 --> 00:55:57,319
Then this happened.

380
00:55:57,600 --> 00:56:01,639
This Pox-Eclipse happened, and it's
finished. It isn't there anymore.

381
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:06,557
You got to understand
that this is home...

382
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:09,914
...and there's no Tomorrow Land...

383
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:12,152
...and I ain't Captain Walker.

384
00:56:42,640 --> 00:56:44,312
This is it!

385
00:58:24,680 --> 00:58:26,432
TUBBA:
We's loaded and waiting, Captain.

386
00:58:26,680 --> 00:58:29,638
MR. SKYFISH: We got the wind
up our arse, Captain. Let's go!

387
01:00:13,480 --> 01:00:15,436
Who's coming?
We's pulling a leaving.

388
01:00:16,000 --> 01:00:19,788
There ain't gonna be no leavings.
All that's just jerking time.

389
01:00:20,040 --> 01:00:21,268
We's working it different.

390
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:24,638
Ain't you seen nothing?
He couldn't catch the wind.

391
01:00:24,960 --> 01:00:27,838
There weren't no skyrafting.
There won't be no salvage.

392
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:30,833
This is our Tomorrow-morrow Land.
He's proof of that.

393
01:00:31,120 --> 01:00:35,830
Program! All of you program.
If he ain't Captain Walker, who is he?

394
01:00:36,520 --> 01:00:39,239
SA VANNAH: He ain't no different
to us. He slogged it on foot.

395
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:42,070
If he can get here,
we can get back.

396
01:00:42,400 --> 01:00:43,992
He ain't much bigger than us.

397
01:00:44,320 --> 01:00:46,629
Copilot did it.
So why can't we?

398
01:00:46,880 --> 01:00:49,110
That's the trick of it.
Who's coming?

399
01:00:50,080 --> 01:00:53,117
Across the nothing?
Don't you 'member?

400
01:00:53,640 --> 01:00:56,632
When you finded him,
he were half jumped by Mr. Dead.

401
01:00:56,880 --> 01:00:59,553
Nobody's saying
it ain't a hard slog.

402
01:00:59,840 --> 01:01:02,479
If we wants the knowing,
it ain't an easy ride.

403
01:01:02,720 --> 01:01:04,517
SLAKE:
There ain't no knowing!

404
01:01:04,760 --> 01:01:08,958
There ain't no skyraft and no sonic.
You slog out there to nothing!

405
01:01:09,320 --> 01:01:10,548
Worse than nothing.

406
01:01:11,040 --> 01:01:14,271
